# LF everywhere — in the object store and in every working tree, on every
# platform. Declared here rather than left to core.autocrlf/core.eol because
# config is per-machine and does not travel: without this line the policy holds
# only for a developer who happens to have configured it globally, and CI or a
# default Windows clone (autocrlf=true) would produce CRLF working trees.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Exemptions below. ORDER MATTERS: in .gitattributes the LAST matching line
# wins, so every `-text` override must stay beneath the `*` rule above.
# `-text` disables conversion entirely and keeps bytes verbatim.

# The CRLF fixture must keep its CRLF line endings verbatim.
test/fixtures/corpus/docs/windows-notes.md -text
# Golden output is byte-exact LF.
test/fixtures/golden/*.ttl -text
